                    <h2 class="text-center">AlertBot
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>AlertBot is a service used by hundreds of the world's top retailers to monitor website performance.  The service alerts users when their sites have problems which require attention, and reports many useful statistics to them in a multitude of ways.  Dozens of reports can be accessed through the service's Manager site, or they can be emailed to account users weekly.  The AlertBot brand has earned the trust of many noteworthy customers including Sony, IBM, Dell, Disney, and the United States Marines.</p>
                    <p>Since 2009, I have been the lead developer on all software, database solutions, and websites for AlertBot.  Most of the work has been accomplished with Microsoft products, including the .NET Framework and SQL Server.</p><p>Some of the projects I've worked on include, but are not limited to:</p>  
                    <ul>
                      <li>a Manager website which allows users to maintain all aspects of their accounts</li>
                      <li>the testing agent from which we monitor all of our clients' sites</li>
                      <li>a Selenium based "recorder" which allows our customers to record scripts that simulate what a typical user of their site would do on a visit to their page</li>
                      <li>a testing module that reproduces these scripts within a real web browser</li>
                      <li>a custom load balancer for our complex testing network which spans the globe</li>
                      <li>dozens of analytical reports that inform our clients on the performance of their websites</li>
                      <li>our databases which contain hundreds of tables, views, and procedures</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The AlertBot brand has been the primary concern of my professional career since graduating from college, and I am immensely proud of the product.</p>
