                    <h2 class="text-center">Eve Watch
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>Eve Watch is an app on the Google Play store designed for players of the popular multiplayer game, Eve Online.  Eve Online is a game set in space, where players are pilots of ships that can fill roles such as miners, pirates, traders, or soldiers.  The game is set in a persistent universe, so the game is always running, even if you're not logged in.  Taking a note from my work on AlertBot, I decided to create an app for Eve Online players that would send them notifications when certain events occurred in-game.  Since Eve Online is a persistent universe, many important things can happen while the player is not logged in to the game.  For example, a user's personal space station could come under attack by a rival group of players.  In this case, a player could lose his (very) expensive property without ever having a chance to defend it.  Eve Watch can be configured to send an alert directly to the player's Android device when such an event occurs, giving them a chance to defend their territory.  In fact, the app can send different notifications for over 140 in-game events.</p>
                    <p>The app was written in Java, and was created for two reasons.  First, I wanted to get some exposure to mobile app development and using APIs.  Second, I was a huge fan of Eve Online at the time of the app's creation, and I wanted to contribute to the community.</p>
                    <p>View the app's page <%= link_to "on Google Play.",   "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.evewatch" %></p>
                    <p>Source code available <%= link_to "on Github.", "https://github.com/LayfieldK/eve_watch" %></p>
