                    <h2 class="text-center">Popular Opinion
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>Something that many people take for granted on the Internet is just how quickly you can get answers to your questions.  What used to take a trip to the library or at least opening an encyclopedia, can now be discovered in mere moments.  Popular Opinion is an idea that uses this functionality of the web in a slightly different manner.  Instead of searching for factual information through Google, Wikipedia, or any other source, users can ask a subjective question to other users and receive a notification when a concensus has been made.  Where should I go for dinner tonight?  What hairstyle should I ask for the next time I visit a stylist?  What new TV show should I watch?  All of these questions can be presented to other users of the site, and the asking user can get live feedback to his question rather than web pages that are weeks, months, or even years old.</p>
                    <p>Currently, Popular Opinion is in a very early stage of development, but the project is being constructed with Ruby On Rails.</p>
