                    <h2 class="text-center">Zombie Simulator
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>Many games, movies, tv shows, and books tell the story of a post-apocalyptic world overrun with zombies.  The idea has been around for at least fifty years and it has seen a surge in popularity within the last decade.  One thing that seems to go overlooked in many cases is the actual spread of the zombie infection.  At most, you see a few people get bit at the beginning of an outbreak and then we fast forward to a time when the zombies have all but wiped out humanity.  I think that there is a lot of potential for storytelling at the time of the main crisis event of a zombie invasion, and that is where this project came from.  This project aims to show the spread of a zombie infection from a handful of infected individuals to a much larger population.</p>
                    <p>When I first loaded up Unreal Engine 4 to see how video game engines worked, this was my first idea.  It was the very first thing I decided to try to create.  So I took the default UE4 character model and created three alternate versions of it.  One, a civilian with the goal of running away from zombies for as long as possible.  Two, a zombie, searching for and infecting anything not already undead.  And Three, a cop, able to shoot zombies in an effort to protect the civilians.  When the program starts, the user gets a bird's eye view of the zombies chasing down cops and civilians until none remain.  This was a very simple idea, but it is an idea with so much potential for growth and development that I can never fully leave it alone.  I intend to expand upon for years to come.</p>
