                    <h2 class="text-center">Legionary Man
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>When I was a kid, I played my NES every day.  My favorite game series was always Mega Man.  I loved how challenging the games were, and how it rewarded you for thinking about what types of weapons might work well against different types of enemies and bosses.  While experimenting with Unreal Engine's Paper2D technology, I decided that it would be fun to make a game like Mega Man.  I decided to cross that idea with my love for ancient Roman history to create Legionary Man.  Legionary Man is a sidescrolling action platformer where you play as a soldier of Rome tasked with defeating the enemies of Rome before they destroy your beloved city.</p>
                    <p>I intend to create this game in stages.  First and most difficult, I will create one complete level of the game.  This will include sound effects, music, background art, character and enemy art, and of course a well thought out level design.  Once this is accomplished, additional levels will be created by following the existing pattern.  Eventually, this may just turn out to a completed game ready for others to enjoy.  For me, working on a classic sidescroller with an ancient Roman theme is already exciting and fulfilling.</p>
