                    <h2 class="text-center">Knight Runner
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>A popular trend on phone app stores is to create an "endless" or "infinite" runner.  These games generally involve your character constantly running, moving faster and faster as the game goes on.  The player's goal is to avoid obstacles for as long as possible in order to get a high score.  Knight Runner is an endless runner created as an experiment to test the capabilities and usage of Unreal Engine 4's Paper2D technology.  I bought a cheap pack of art assets on UE4's marketplace and dove in.  In the game, your character dashes across the screen faster and faster as the game progresses with you jumping or sliding anytime you need to clear obstacles.</p>
                    <p>The game was never given full polish of a proper UI, but it was only ever meant to be an experiment.  It also tends to make me sick when I play it too long because of the very fast repetition of the background design, but I am still very happy with the results of this project, as it gave me the confidence to create a proper sidescrolling game in Legionary Man.</p>
